 understood as a problem of individual merit, meanness, effort, or emotion rather than a structural issue requiring deeper intervention. Surface-level sensitivity allows American High to avoid ";political"; topics related to social inequality based on race, sex, gender, or class. Being nice to each other, Pascoe reveals, does not serve these students or solve the broader issues we face; however, a true politics of care just might.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEducation, SecondaryxSocial aspectszUnited Statesy21st century. 0aEqualityzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aHigh school studentsxPolitical activityzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aKindness. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520396753?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520396753423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520396753/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles